cluster_relations.rel_desc: Butterflies undergo the butterfly life cycle as a transformative process.
Caterpillars contribute to the biological process of pollination.
The caterpillar is a stage that participates in the butterfly's life cycle.

qualifiers.TemporalQualifier: early stages of butterfly life cycle
qualifiers.OtherQualifier: LifecycleRole: larval stage prior to pupa

cluster_relations.rel_desc: Adult butterflies participate in and play an important role in pollination.
Adult butterflies engage in reproduction during the adult stage.

args.canonical_rel_desc: Connects an organism or life stage to a biological process in which it participates, contributes, or which it undergoes as part of its life cycle or functional role.
args.justification: In all five relations, the subject (butterflies, their life stages) is a continuant that takes part in a biological process (butterfly life cycle, pollination, reproduction). Although the raw labels vary (undergoes_process, contributes_to_process, engages_in, participates_in), the common semantics is participation in or undergoing a biological process, so a single canonical predicate improves consistency.

Each relation links a biological entity (organism or life stage) to a biological process in which it participates or which it undergoes (life cycle, pollination, reproduction). This is a classic participation-in-process family of relations.

These relations capture entities actively taking part in processes (life cycle progression, pollination, reproduction), which fits an agent/participation dimension better than composition, identity, or pure association.
